WEBVTT

00:03.291 --> 00:05.083
♪ OHHH OHHH OHHH ♪

00:06.792 --> 00:09.792
(whirring)

00:13.083 --> 00:16.792
OH, THE--THE RANGE OF MOVEMENT
IS AMAZING.

00:16.834 --> 00:18.917
YOU THINK THAT'S GOOD.
HEY, PETE.

00:18.959 --> 00:21.792
GO ON. TOSS IT TO COLIN.
COME ON. DON'T BE AFRAID
TO PUT A LITTLE HEAT ON IT.

00:21.834 --> 00:24.041
I'M PRETTY GOOD.

00:24.083 --> 00:26.542
(laughs)
NICE CATCH.

00:26.583 --> 00:29.542
I CONNECTED THE ARM DIRECTLY
TO COLIN'S NERVOUS SYSTEM.

00:29.583 --> 00:32.625
THE BRAIN THINKS "CATCH
THE BALL," AND THE HAND DOES IT.
THE GUYS IN MY UNIT
WOULD FREAK.

00:32.667 --> 00:34.792
OH, WERE--WERE YOU
IN IRAQ?
AFGHANISTAN.

00:34.834 --> 00:36.041
YEAH.

00:36.083 --> 00:38.375
(sighs) FEEL FREE
TO USE WORDS

00:38.417 --> 00:40.834
LIKE "GENIUS"
OR "BRILLIANT" AT WILL.

00:40.875 --> 00:43.125
I DON'T HAVE TO
'CAUSE YOU JUST DID.

00:43.166 --> 00:45.458
IT WAS REALLY NICE
TO MEET YOU,

00:45.500 --> 00:47.750
AND, UH,
GOOD LUCK WITH YOUR ARM.

00:47.792 --> 00:50.041
AH. (groans)

00:50.083 --> 00:52.000
(Pete) YOU OKAY?
NO, SOMETHING--

00:52.041 --> 00:55.625
OH, IT BURNS.
HELP HIM, OR HE'S GONNA
PULL OUT THE NEURO CONNECTORS.

00:55.667 --> 00:56.875
MM. AH.

00:56.917 --> 00:59.000
(pants)

00:59.041 --> 01:00.834
AH.

01:00.875 --> 01:03.166
YOU IMPLANTED A BOLT
IN HIS ARM?
OSSEOUS INTEGRATION.

01:03.208 --> 01:06.041
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
TO CARRY THE WEIGHT.
I KNOW WHAT IT IS.
IT'S ALSO ILLEGAL.

01:06.083 --> 01:09.000
IN THIS COUNTRY.
I SENT HIM TO SWEDEN.
AH!

01:09.041 --> 01:11.709
AH! MM.
OKAY, IT'S INFECTED.
HE'S BURNING UP.

01:11.750 --> 01:14.041
WE'VE GOTTA GET HIM
TO THE HOSPITAL.

01:14.083 --> 01:15.709
(wheelchair motor whirs)

01:15.750 --> 01:17.709
(Dell) OKAY, WELL,
MAYA'S IN YOUR OFFICE.

01:17.750 --> 01:20.625
SHE WOULDN'T EVEN LOOK AT ME
IN THE CAR ON THE WAY OVER HERE,

01:20.667 --> 01:23.709
AND NOW YOU GOT SAM AND NAOMI
IN THE CONFERENCE ROOM.

01:23.750 --> 01:27.208
DO YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON?
NO, I CAN'T, DELL.
I WISH I COULD, BUT I CAN'T.

01:27.250 --> 01:29.208
GUYS, UM,
VERY PREGNANT WOMAN

01:29.250 --> 01:31.750
SQUATTING UP AND DOWN
IN THE HALLWAY?
NOT MINE.

01:31.792 --> 01:34.917
SHE'S MINE. LYNN McDONALD. SHE'S
COMMITTED TO NATURAL CHILDBIRTH.

01:34.959 --> 01:36.917
SHE'S BEEN IN LABOR
FOR TWO DAYS.

01:36.959 --> 01:39.667
HER WATER FINALLY BROKE
LAST NIGHT.
OOH. THIS ISN'T WORKING.

01:39.709 --> 01:41.667
DO YOU HAVE ANYTHING SPICY
IN THE FRIDGE?

01:41.709 --> 01:43.750
LIKE MAYBE--MAYBE
A CHIMICHANGA, HUH?

01:43.792 --> 01:46.834
THAT'LL SPEED UP
THE LABOR, RIGHT?
YEAH, I'LL ORDER YOU SOMETHING.

01:46.875 --> 01:48.834
YEAH. OKAY, BABY, COME OUT.

01:48.875 --> 01:51.458
(exhales deeply)
AND COME OUT.

01:51.500 --> 01:53.500
(exhales)
AND... COME OUT.

01:53.542 --> 01:55.834
WELL, LET'S GO CHECK OUT
YOUR PROGRESS.
AND COME OUT.

01:55.875 --> 01:59.959
OKAY, ADDISON. WHAT'S THIS
IMPORTANT CASE THAT, UH...

02:00.000 --> 02:01.667
HEY, MAYA GIRL.
HEY.

02:01.709 --> 02:04.500
WHAT'S UP? WAIT. DID YOU HAVE
A HALF A DAY TODAY?
NO, NO, NO.

02:04.542 --> 02:07.792
WAS I SUPPOSED TO--
NO, NO, NO. I ALWAYS KEEP
THE HALF DAYS IN MY CALENDAR.

02:07.834 --> 02:11.000
I KEEP 'EM
IN MY CALENDAR, TOO.
IT'S NOT A HALF DAY.

02:11.041 --> 02:14.500
MAYA HAS SOMETHING
THAT SHE NEEDS TO TELL YOU.

02:16.125 --> 02:18.500
(clears throat)

02:20.041 --> 02:21.959
I...

02:25.709 --> 02:26.792
UM...

02:26.834 --> 02:29.375
(clears throat)

02:29.417 --> 02:31.917
I...

02:36.083 --> 02:38.542
MAYA'S PREGNANT.

02:43.875 --> 02:45.917
NO, SHE'S NOT.

02:45.959 --> 02:47.792
HOW?

02:47.834 --> 02:50.417
WHEN DID YOU START
HAVING S--

02:50.458 --> 02:52.834
WAIT. NO. NO, OKAY.
THIS IS--THIS ISN'T POSSIBLE.

02:52.875 --> 02:55.500
WE DISCUSSED THIS.
WE DISCUSSED BIRTH CONTROL.

02:55.542 --> 02:57.208
YOUR--TWO DOCTORS.

02:57.250 --> 03:00.041
BOTH YOUR PARENTS ARE DOCTORS.
HOW COULD YOU BE PREGNANT?

03:00.083 --> 03:01.792
HOW COULD THIS BE HAPPENING?

03:01.834 --> 03:04.041
WHAT WERE--
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

03:04.083 --> 03:06.166
HEY, WHERE YOU GOING?
OUR DAUGHTER JUST TOLD US

03:06.208 --> 03:08.375
THAT--THAT--THAT
SHE IS PREGNANT.

03:08.417 --> 03:10.375
WE NEED TO TALK ABOUT THIS.
I CAN'T.

03:10.417 --> 03:13.583
MOM--
NAOMI, WE ARE HER PARENTS.

03:13.625 --> 03:16.417
I CAN'T.

03:30.625 --> 03:31.792
(sighs)

03:31.834 --> 03:34.041
NAOMI WALKED AWAY.

03:34.083 --> 03:37.041
OUR DAUGHTER IS PREGNANT,
AND NAOMI WALKED AWAY.
I KNOW.

03:37.083 --> 03:40.041
SHE'S IN SHOCK.
SHE'S DEALING WITH IT.
I'M SUPPOSED TO JUST WAIT

03:40.083 --> 03:42.166
UNTIL SHE DECIDES
THAT SHE'S READY?

03:42.208 --> 03:44.875
WE NEED TO TALK
TO OUR DAUGHTER NOW.

03:44.917 --> 03:46.875
SAM, THIS ISN'T
THE FIRST TIME

03:46.917 --> 03:49.291
I'VE DELIVERED
THIS KIND OF NEWS.

03:49.333 --> 03:53.041
PEOPLE NEED TIME. GIVE...
GIVE NAOMI SOME TIME.

03:53.083 --> 03:55.041
COLIN, YOU HAVE
A SEVERE INFECTION.

03:55.083 --> 03:56.875
HOW LONG
HAS IT BEEN HURTING?

03:56.917 --> 04:00.917
A MONTH. I THOUGHT
IT WAS NORMAL PAIN.

04:00.959 --> 04:03.875
AND I WAS AFRAID
THAT IF IT WAS THE BOLT,

04:03.917 --> 04:07.000
THEN I COULDN'T KEEP THE ARM.
WELL, DR. WILDER FEELS
THE BOLT SHOULD COME OUT.

04:07.041 --> 04:10.667
NO. CAN'T WE DO
MORE ANTIBIOTICS OR SOMETHING?
WELL, WHAT DO YOU SAY,
DR. WILDER?

04:10.709 --> 04:12.667
YOU SPECIALIZE
IN INFECTIOUS DISEASE.

04:12.709 --> 04:15.458
YOU KNOW ALTERNATIVE TREATMENTS.
WHAT ARE HIS OPTIONS?

04:15.500 --> 04:18.041
THERE HAS TO BE
SOMETHING UP YOUR SLEEVE

04:18.083 --> 04:21.250
SINCE YOU HAVE TWO OF THEM.
THERE ARE
EXPERIMENTAL PROTOCOLS,

04:21.291 --> 04:24.041
BUT THE F.D.A. HASN'T COMPLETED
SAFETY STUDIES,

04:24.083 --> 04:26.041
AND THERE ARE REPORTS
OF SEVERE SIDE EFFECTS.

04:26.083 --> 04:29.041
I'M SORRY. THE BOLT IS
THE SOURCE OF THE INFECTION,

04:29.083 --> 04:31.125
AND THE SAFEST THING TO DO
IS REMOVE IT

04:31.166 --> 04:33.625
BEFORE THE INFECTION SPREADS.

04:33.667 --> 04:36.208
BEFORE I DEPLOYED,
I GOT ENGAGED.

04:36.250 --> 04:38.208
WE WROTE LETTERS,
WE PLANNED THE WHOLE THING,

04:38.250 --> 04:40.750
RIGHT DOWN TO THE DANCE
THAT WE'RE GOING TO DO,

04:40.792 --> 04:43.041
WHICH REQUIRES ME
TO DIP HER TO THE FLOOR.

04:43.083 --> 04:44.959
NOW I'M LIVING UP
TO MY PART OF THIS.

04:45.000 --> 04:48.000
I'M GOING TO HOLD HER
IN MY ARMS--BOTH ARMS--

04:48.041 --> 04:50.959
AND I'M GOING TO DANCE WITH HER
THE WAY I PROMISED.

04:51.000 --> 04:53.458
YOU CAME BACK ALIVE.
YOU'RE HEALTHY AND ALIVE.

04:53.500 --> 04:56.458
I KNOW YOU PLANNED FOR MORE,
BUT I CANNOT TREAT YOU

04:56.500 --> 04:59.291
IN A WAY THAT WILL
JEOPARDIZE YOUR HEALTH.
DR. WILDER--

04:59.333 --> 05:02.000
COLIN, THIS INFECTION
COULD KILL YOU.

05:02.041 --> 05:05.041
I KNOW THAT'S NOT
WHAT YOUR FIANCéE WANTS.

05:05.083 --> 05:08.083
(Violet) WHY DO THEY DO THIS?

05:08.125 --> 05:10.709
WHY DOES THE HOSPITAL
KEEP SENDING ME SAMPLES?

05:10.750 --> 05:14.583
IT'S LIKE "GASLIGHT,"
BUT WITH BABY STUFF.

05:14.625 --> 05:17.875
"GASLIGHT"? FAMOUS MOVIE?

05:17.917 --> 05:21.041
NEVER SAW IT.
INGRID BERGMAN.

05:21.083 --> 05:24.041
HER HUSBAND
TRIES TO DRIVE HER CRAZY.
UH, WHEN THE PETERMANS
GET HERE,

05:24.083 --> 05:26.208
WILL YOU PUT THEM
IN EXAM ROOM THREE?
I'M USING EXAM ROOM THREE.

05:26.250 --> 05:28.959
OH, ACTUALLY ROOM THREE
IS FOR PEDIATRICS.

05:29.000 --> 05:32.875
AND I HAVE A 7 YEAR OLD WITH
A URINARY TRACT INFECTION.

05:34.083 --> 05:39.041
IT'S--IT'S ABOUT A MARRIAGE
THAT ENDS BADLY.

05:39.083 --> 05:40.166
"GASLIGHT."

05:51.000 --> 05:52.166
MARSHA.

05:52.208 --> 05:54.000
HI. VIOLET TURNER.

05:54.041 --> 05:55.208
UH, HERE'S THE SITUATION--

05:55.250 --> 05:57.458
I DON'T WANT
ANY MORE BABY STUFF.

05:57.500 --> 06:00.333
SO NO DIAPER CREAM SAMPLES.

06:00.375 --> 06:02.041
I'VE--I'VE CALLED,
I'VE E-MAILED,

06:02.083 --> 06:05.000
I'VE MAIL-MAILED
FOR THE PAST SIX MONTHS,

06:05.041 --> 06:07.625
BUT THE HOSPITAL
JUST KEEPS SENDING IT.
MOST NEW MOTHERS APPRECIATE
OUR LITTLE FREEBIES.

06:07.667 --> 06:10.625
WELL, I AM NOT A NEW MOTHER.
HOW OLD IS YOUR BABY?

06:10.667 --> 06:12.834
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.

06:12.875 --> 06:15.875
I AM NOT A NEW OR AN OLD
OR ANY KIND OF MOTHER.

06:15.917 --> 06:18.125
I DON'T HAVE A BABY ANYMORE.

06:18.166 --> 06:20.041
OH. OH, MY GOD.

06:20.083 --> 06:22.041
I'M SO SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.

06:22.083 --> 06:24.041
THEY'RE GOD'S
LITTLEST ANGELS,

06:24.083 --> 06:26.250
THE ONES WE LOSE.

06:26.291 --> 06:29.041
COULD YOU JUST GET
THE FORM?

06:29.083 --> 06:31.041
OF COURSE.

06:31.083 --> 06:34.417
I'M SORRY, TOO,
FOR YOUR LOSS.

06:34.458 --> 06:36.417
OH, NO, NO. IT'S JUST--
I-I WAS JUST--

06:36.458 --> 06:38.834
NO, NO, NO. YOU DON'T
HAVE TO EXPLAIN. I-I GET IT.

06:38.875 --> 06:41.667
I-I--
I LOST MY WIFE TODAY.

06:41.709 --> 06:43.041
OH, MY GOD.

06:43.083 --> 06:46.041
A SENTENCE YOU NEVER THINK
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO SAY,

06:46.083 --> 06:49.041
YOU KNOW, "I LOST--
I LOST MY WIFE."

06:49.083 --> 06:51.041
AND, UH, EVERY TIME
YOU SAY IT,

06:51.083 --> 06:53.166
YOU THINK YOU'RE NOT GONNA
BE ABLE TO BREATHE,

06:53.208 --> 06:55.917
AND IT'S LIKE--IT'S LIKE
SOMEBODY SHOT YOU OR SOMETHING.

06:55.959 --> 06:57.917
AND THEN I--AND THEN I HEAR

06:57.959 --> 07:00.041
THAT YOU LOST YOUR CHILD--
YOUR BABY--AND IT'S--

07:00.083 --> 07:02.125
IT, LIKE, GIVES IT
PERSPECTIVE, YOU KNOW?

07:02.166 --> 07:05.125
IT--IT'S--IT'S--IT HELPS ME
TO KNOW YOU LOST YOUR CHILD.

07:05.166 --> 07:08.125
AND I KNOW THAT'S
A HORRIBLE THING TO SAY TO YOU.

07:08.166 --> 07:11.041
UM... MY WIFE'S DEAD,
AND I'VE OFFENDED YOU,

07:11.083 --> 07:13.041
AND I'M SORRY...

07:13.083 --> 07:14.667
FOR YOUR LOSS.

07:14.709 --> 07:17.041
NO, NO. I'M--I'M SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

07:17.083 --> 07:20.291
THEY GAVE ME THIS BAG
WITH HER... BELONGINGS.

07:20.333 --> 07:22.041
IT'S...

07:22.083 --> 07:24.041
(exhales) IT'S FUNNY.

07:24.083 --> 07:27.041
I THOUGHT THERE'D BE MORE
TO TAKE HOME.

07:27.083 --> 07:30.041
DO YOU NEED...

07:30.083 --> 07:33.125
CAN I HELP YOU?
IS THERE ANYTHING I CAN DO?

07:33.166 --> 07:35.166
UH, NO. NO, NO.
I-I'M JUST WAITING.

07:35.208 --> 07:37.458
A FRIEND'S PICKING ME UP,
SO...

07:37.500 --> 07:39.041
OKAY.

07:39.083 --> 07:41.500
WELL...

07:41.542 --> 07:43.500
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU.

07:43.542 --> 07:45.458
I'M NATHAN PILSMAN.

07:45.500 --> 07:47.041
VIOLET TURNER.

07:47.083 --> 07:49.041
IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU,
VIOLET TURNER.

07:49.083 --> 07:51.375
WELL, NOT NICE,
BUT... IT'S NICE.

07:56.083 --> 07:58.041
(whirring)

07:58.083 --> 08:01.083
(footsteps approach)

08:01.125 --> 08:03.083
YOU CAN'T WALK.

08:03.125 --> 08:05.250
YOU'RE BLACK.
WHAT GAME ARE WE PLAYING?

08:05.291 --> 08:08.750
THE DAY
THAT YOU FOUND OUT...

08:08.792 --> 08:11.583
WHEN THEY TOLD YOU THAT,
UH, YOUR LEGS--

08:11.625 --> 08:13.959
THAT YOU WOULD--YOU WOULD
NEVER WALK AGAIN,

08:14.000 --> 08:16.625
THAT MUST HAVE BEEN
THE WORST DAY OF YOUR LIFE.

08:16.667 --> 08:19.500
HOW DID YOU DEAL WITH IT?

08:19.542 --> 08:22.834
WHY WOULD YOU ASSUME THAT
THAT WAS MY WORST DAY?

08:22.875 --> 08:25.625
LOSING MY LEGS
CHANGED MY LIFE,

08:25.667 --> 08:28.083
BUT, UH, IT CERTAINLY
DIDN'T RUIN IT.

08:28.125 --> 08:30.333
THERE'S A PERIOD
OF ADJUSTMENT,

08:30.375 --> 08:34.041
BUT... YOU DEAL WITH IT.

08:34.083 --> 08:36.834
YOU'RE FULL OF CRAP.

08:41.291 --> 08:43.041
(elevator bell dings)

08:43.083 --> 08:46.041
(indistinct conversations)

08:51.792 --> 08:54.792
NAOMI, WHAT--WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

08:57.083 --> 08:59.041
MOM, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:59.083 --> 09:00.750
WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:00.792 --> 09:02.917
NAOMI,
WHAT IS GOING ON?

09:04.208 --> 09:06.667
I NEED YOU TO GIVE MAYA
AN ABORTION.
WHAT?

09:06.709 --> 09:10.000
NAI.
MOM, NO.
I DON'T WANT AN ABORTION.

09:10.041 --> 09:12.834
I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU WANT.
BUT, MOM--

09:12.875 --> 09:14.667
GIVE HER AN ABORTION.

09:18.083 --> 09:20.041
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I SLAPPED HER.

09:20.083 --> 09:21.667
I HIT MY CHILD.

09:21.709 --> 09:23.208
YOU WERE UPSET, CLEARLY.

09:23.250 --> 09:25.250
IT'S NOT AN EASY THING
TO DEAL WITH.

09:25.291 --> 09:29.041
I KNOW, I KNOW, BUT I...
WELL, I CAN'T--I LOST IT.

09:29.083 --> 09:31.792
BUT C-CAN YOU BELIEVE HER?

09:31.834 --> 09:36.291
CAN YOU BELIEVE HER
SAYING NO TO ME?

09:36.333 --> 09:38.000
WHAT?

09:38.041 --> 09:40.000
YOU ORDERED HER
TO HAVE AN ABORTION.

09:40.041 --> 09:43.000
SO PUTTING ASIDE THE FACT THAT
YOU ARE PERSONALLY AGAINST IT--

09:43.041 --> 09:46.041
YOU CAN'T MAKE SOMEONE
HAVE AN ABORTION, NAI.

09:46.083 --> 09:49.709
NO, NO, NO. THIS IS--THIS--THIS
IS NOT UP FOR DISCUSSION.

09:49.750 --> 09:52.709
I THINK IT NEEDS TO BE.
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT? IF YOU'RE
NOT GONNA DO IT, THAT'S FINE.

09:52.750 --> 09:56.291
I WILL FIND ANOTHER DOCTOR
WHO WILL.
OKAY, I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHO I'M TALKING TO RIGHT NOW.

09:56.333 --> 09:59.041
THIS IS NOT YOU.
IT'S THE OPPOSITE OF YOU.

09:59.083 --> 10:00.667
YOU--YOU GIVE PEOPLE BABIES,

10:00.709 --> 10:03.959
AND WHETHER OR NOT I AGREE
WITH YOUR STAND ON THIS ISSUE,

10:04.000 --> 10:07.917
THIS ISN'T YOU.
DON'T DO SOMETHING NOW THAT YOU
WILL HATE YOURSELF FOR LATER.

10:07.959 --> 10:11.083
DO YOU HATE YOURSELF
FOR YOUR ABORTIONS?

10:11.125 --> 10:12.917
EITHER OF YOU?

10:12.959 --> 10:16.083
NO, I DON'T HATE MYSELF.
BUT I DO THINK ABOUT IT.

10:16.125 --> 10:19.083
IT STAYS WITH YOU EVEN IF YOU
DO IT FOR THE RIGHT REASONS,

10:19.125 --> 10:22.250
AND IT IS NOT A CASUAL DECISION
THAT YOU CAN MAKE FOR MAYA.

10:22.291 --> 10:26.041
THIS--THIS IS MY FAMILY.
YOU DO NOT JUDGE MY FAMILY!

10:26.083 --> 10:28.750
WE'RE NOT JUDGING.
YOU KNOW THAT.
LOOK, THIS HAS HIT YOU HARD,

10:28.792 --> 10:31.291
AND THAT CAN MAKE YOU CHANGE
WHAT YOU BELIEVE--
STOP IT. STOP IT.

10:31.333 --> 10:33.291
(voice breaking) STOP ACTING
LIKE YOU UNDERSTAND,

10:33.333 --> 10:34.750
BECAUSE YOU DON'T.

10:34.792 --> 10:36.750
YOU DON'T.
THIS IS MY CHILD.

10:36.792 --> 10:39.792
THIS IS MY CHILD WE ARE
TALKING ABOUT, MY CHILD...

10:39.834 --> 10:42.875
WHO I'VE DONE EVERYTHING IN
MY POWER TO RAISE AND PROTECT.

10:42.917 --> 10:44.875
AND NOW SHE'S GONE
AND DONE SOMETHING STUPID--

10:44.917 --> 10:46.875
STUPID--
THAT'S GONNA RUIN HER LIFE,

10:46.917 --> 10:48.875
AND I'M NOT
GONNA LET THAT HAPPEN.

10:48.917 --> 10:51.709
I AM HER MOTHER.
I AM HER MOTHER.
NAOMI--

10:51.750 --> 10:54.000
YOU HAVE NO RIGHT. YOU HAVE
NO MORAL HIGH GROUND.

10:54.041 --> 10:56.834
YOU WALKED AWAY
FROM YOUR CHILD.

10:56.875 --> 11:00.000
IF YOU CAN LIVE WITH THAT,
I CAN LIVE WITH THIS.

11:01.625 --> 11:04.041
SHE'S JUST UPSET. YOU--

11:04.083 --> 11:05.709
I KNOW.

11:05.750 --> 11:09.041
(knocks on doorjamb)
(clears throat) UH,
I KNOW THIS IS A BAD TIME,

11:09.083 --> 11:12.041
BUT MY PATIENT--I-I COULD
REALLY USE YOUR HELP.

11:12.083 --> 11:15.041
YES. PLEASE.
TELL ME SHE NEEDS SURGERY.

11:15.083 --> 11:17.208
THAT I CAN DO.

11:22.625 --> 11:24.834
OH, DON'T NEED YOUR HELP
OPENING A DOOR.

11:24.875 --> 11:27.375
YOU'RE NOT VERY GOOD
AT TAKING HELP, ARE YOU?

11:27.417 --> 11:29.875
OH, ACTUALLY, I AM. YOUR IDEA
ABOUT EXPERIMENTAL PROTOCOLS?

11:29.917 --> 11:31.458
I CONTACTED MY FRIEND

11:31.500 --> 11:34.041
AT THE F.D.A.,
GOT THE INFO, WENT WITH IT.

11:34.083 --> 11:37.041
YOU'RE NOT TAKING OUT
COLIN'S BOLT?
YOU MIGHT BE AFRAID TO TAKE
A RISK, BUT I'M NOT.

11:37.083 --> 11:39.000
I ASSUMED
NAOMI BROUGHT YOU IN

11:39.041 --> 11:40.625
BECAUSE YOU WERE
JUST AS CUTTING-EDGE

11:40.667 --> 11:42.333
AS EVERYONE ELSE AROUND HERE.

11:42.375 --> 11:45.041
I DIDN'T REALIZE YOU WERE
THE SAFE ALTERNATIVE.

11:45.083 --> 11:47.041
ALL RIGHT, YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU--HEY. HEY. HEY.

11:47.083 --> 11:50.041
YOU CAN'T JUST SAY SOMETHING
LIKE THAT AND ROLL AWAY.

11:50.083 --> 11:52.750
CAN'T HEAR YOU
OVER THE NOISE OF MY CHAIR.
(elevator bell dings)

11:52.792 --> 11:54.875
HEY, PETE.

11:54.917 --> 11:56.417
MAYA IS PREGNANT.

11:56.458 --> 11:59.000
SAM NEEDS TO DRINK.
YOU IN?

12:02.542 --> 12:04.083
(Lynn) OH!

12:04.125 --> 12:06.083
UH, LYNN'S IN A LOT OF PAIN.

12:06.125 --> 12:08.083
SHE SHOWS NO SIGN
OF FETAL DISTRESS,

12:08.125 --> 12:11.250
BUT HER LABOR
ISN'T PROGRESSING.
I THOUGHT
AFTER MY WATER BROKE...

12:11.291 --> 12:14.250
WELL, I CAN GIVE YOU OXYTOCIN
TO SPEED UP THE LABOR

12:14.291 --> 12:17.041
AND SOMETHING FOR THE PAIN.
MY BIRTH PLAN SAYS NO DRUGS.

12:17.083 --> 12:18.375
LYNN HAS A BIRTH PLAN.

12:18.417 --> 12:20.250
OH, MANY PAGES...

12:20.291 --> 12:22.875
AND SMALL FONT.
YEAH.

12:22.917 --> 12:25.667
I WANT TO EXPERIENCE
MY CHILD'S BIRTH.
UH, LYNN--

12:25.709 --> 12:27.208
I DID MY HOMEWORK, OKAY?

12:27.250 --> 12:29.875
I-I UNDERSTAND
THAT THERE ARE PROCEDURES

12:29.917 --> 12:31.917
THAT, YOU KNOW,
MAY BECOME NECESSARY,

12:31.959 --> 12:34.083
BUT EXCEPT IN A CASE
OF EXTREME EMERGENCY,

12:34.125 --> 12:37.500
YOU KNOW, I WANT TO BE GIVEN
THE OPPORTUNITY TO ACCEPT OR--

12:37.542 --> 12:38.959
OR REFUSE ANY PROCEDURE.

12:39.000 --> 12:40.959
AND AS LONG AS THE BABY'S OKAY,
ALL RIGHT,

12:41.000 --> 12:43.458
I WANT TO HAVE
A NATURAL CHILDBIRTH.

12:43.500 --> 12:47.709
SO TO GET THE LABOR GOING,
I'M WILLING TO TRY WALKING

12:47.750 --> 12:51.041
OR CASTOR OIL
OR NIPPLE STIMULATION--

12:51.083 --> 12:52.959
WELL, IT'S
A LITTLE MORE INVOLVED.

12:53.000 --> 12:55.417
IF YOU FAIL TO PROGRESS
IN YOUR LABOR,

12:55.458 --> 12:58.417
YOU MIGHT WANT TO CONSIDER
A C-SECTION.
NO. NO.

12:58.458 --> 13:01.417
LYNN, LOOK, I KNOW
THIS CAN BE DISAPPOINTING--
I'VE BEEN IN SCREAMING PAIN
FOR HOURS.

13:01.458 --> 13:04.542
I'M NOT--I'M NOT WORRIED
ABOUT BEING DISAPPOINTED.

13:04.583 --> 13:06.959
(grunts)

13:07.000 --> 13:09.583
YOU KNOW, I-I MARRIED
A GREAT GUY.

13:09.625 --> 13:11.875
YOU KNOW,
I WANTED TO HAVE KIDS.

13:11.917 --> 13:14.375
HE WASN'T READY... EVER.

13:14.417 --> 13:18.041
AND... WHEN THE DIVORCE
WAS FINAL,

13:18.083 --> 13:21.041
I DECIDED TO LET LOOSE.

13:21.083 --> 13:23.458
YOU KNOW,
HAVING A BABY ALONE,

13:23.500 --> 13:26.458
BEING PREGNANT BY SOME GUY
THAT I MET AT THE TEQUILA BAR,

13:26.500 --> 13:28.458
IS NOT EVERY GIRL'S DREAM,

13:28.500 --> 13:30.542
BUT THIS IS
WHAT'S HAPPENING, OKAY?

13:30.583 --> 13:32.500
AND I AM HAVING THIS BABY.

13:32.542 --> 13:34.500
SO IS IT TOO MUCH TO ASK

13:34.542 --> 13:37.083
THAT ONE THING
GOES ACCORDING TO PLAN?

13:37.125 --> 13:39.959
(Harper Simon's "Berkeley Girl"
playing)

13:40.000 --> 13:43.041
(Sam) NAOMI HAS LOST HER MIND.

13:43.083 --> 13:47.041
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHO SHE WAS TODAY.
DO YOU WANT MAYA
TO HAVE AN ABORTION?

13:47.083 --> 13:48.500
WELL, THAT'S THE POINT.

13:48.542 --> 13:51.500
I'M A GUY. IT'S--
IT'S--IT'S NOT MY CHOICE.

13:51.542 --> 13:53.500
WELL, RIGHT, BUT DO YOU
WANT HER TO--

13:53.542 --> 13:57.041
DO I--I WANT HER TO NOT
BE PREGNANT IN THE FIRST PLACE.

13:57.083 --> 13:59.125
I WANT HER
TO NEVER HAVE HAD SEX.

13:59.166 --> 14:01.208
I WANT HER TO LIVE IN A WORLD

14:01.250 --> 14:04.041
WHERE THERE ARE CHASTITY BELTS
AND CONVENTS

14:04.083 --> 14:08.375
AND LITTLE BOYS
BY THE NAME OF DINK DON'T EXIST.

14:08.417 --> 14:10.834
THAT--THAT'S WHAT I WANT.

14:10.875 --> 14:13.041
SO DON'T ASK ME
IF I WANT...

14:13.083 --> 14:16.083
MY BABY GIRL
TO HAVE AN ABORTION.

14:16.125 --> 14:18.792
DON'T--DON'T ASK ME THAT.

14:18.834 --> 14:20.458
♪ BLOWIN' DOWN A COUNTRY LANE ♪

14:20.500 --> 14:22.750
BECAUSE THE ANSWER
IS PROBABLY YES.

14:22.792 --> 14:24.583
♪ SHE'S GOT THE STYLE... ♪

14:24.625 --> 14:26.166
BUT IT'S NOT MY CHOICE.

14:26.208 --> 14:28.417
YOU KNOW,
IT'S NOT NAOMI'S EITHER.

14:28.458 --> 14:31.458
LOOK, JUST BE GLAD YOU
AND CHARLOTTE DON'T HAVE A KID.
OH.

14:31.500 --> 14:33.875
ONCE YOU HAVE A CHILD
WITH SOMEONE,

14:33.917 --> 14:36.041
YOU ARE TIED
TO THEM FOREVER,

14:36.083 --> 14:38.750
EVEN IF THEY GO NUTS.
(scoffs)

14:38.792 --> 14:40.959
(laughs)
I'M--I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T...

14:41.000 --> 14:43.333
(laughs)
I DIDN'T MEAN THAT, MAN.

14:43.375 --> 14:47.417
♪ AND THE HILLS OF ECHO PARK ♪

14:47.458 --> 14:51.041
MY DAUGHTER'S PREGNANT.

14:51.083 --> 14:56.041
♪ SHE IS CRINOLINE AND SATIN ♪

14:56.083 --> 14:59.041
♪ SHE IS LEOPARD SKIN
AND LACE ♪

14:59.083 --> 15:00.792
OH, I'M STILL HERE.

15:00.834 --> 15:02.291
BUT THEN, SO ARE YOU.

15:02.333 --> 15:04.667
WELL, I LEFT AND I CAME BACK.

15:04.709 --> 15:08.458
I THOUGHT ABOUT YOU
AND I WAS WORRIED.

15:08.500 --> 15:11.458
YOU DON'T HAVE
A FRIEND COMING, DO YOU?

15:11.500 --> 15:12.500
NO.

15:12.542 --> 15:15.667
I'M NOT READY.

15:15.709 --> 15:17.667
THE THING IS...

15:17.709 --> 15:20.792
I CAN'T LEAVE
WITHOUT MY WIFE.

15:20.834 --> 15:24.542
OBVIOUSLY, I-I CAN'T LEAVE
WITH HER.

15:24.583 --> 15:27.041
SO I CAN'T LEAVE.

15:27.083 --> 15:29.542
♪ ...BERKELEY GIRL ♪

15:29.583 --> 15:31.542
CAN I SIT WITH YOU
FOR A WHILE?

15:31.583 --> 15:33.208
SURE.

15:33.250 --> 15:35.041
♪ ...THE MOON AND THE SUN ♪

15:35.083 --> 15:37.041
♪ OH ♪

15:37.083 --> 15:39.709
♪ AH ♪

15:39.750 --> 15:41.500
DID YOU FEEL THIS WAY

15:41.542 --> 15:45.458
WHEN YOU LOST YOUR CHILD?

15:45.500 --> 15:49.083
WELL... YEAH,
WALKING OUT THAT DOOR

15:49.125 --> 15:51.542
WAS THE HARDEST THING
I EVER DID.

15:51.583 --> 15:53.500
BUT...

15:53.542 --> 15:56.125
YEAH, YEAH, I DID
FEEL THIS WAY.

15:56.166 --> 15:57.709
♪ OOH ♪

15:57.750 --> 16:01.333
♪ OH, BERKELEY GIRL ♪

16:01.375 --> 16:03.583
I HAVE THIS TINGLING

16:03.625 --> 16:06.375
IN--IN MY STUMP,
IN MY SHOULDER AND MY FEET.

16:06.417 --> 16:09.375
IT'S LIKE THEY'RE ASLEEP.
I CAN'T WAKE THEM UP.

16:09.417 --> 16:12.250
(motor whirs)

16:12.291 --> 16:15.041
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

16:15.083 --> 16:17.000
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

16:17.041 --> 16:19.000
UH, A SIDE EFFECT
OF THE ANTIBIOTICS

16:19.041 --> 16:20.750
IS NEUROTOXICITY--
NERVE DAMAGE.

16:20.792 --> 16:22.875
IS THIS WHAT DR. WILDER
WAS AFRAID OF?

16:22.917 --> 16:26.542
NO. I'M GONNA LOWER THE DOSAGE
ON THE ANTIBIOTIC.

16:26.583 --> 16:28.750
THAT SHOULD LESSEN
THE EFFECT.

16:28.792 --> 16:30.750
WE'LL GIVE IT A SHOT.

16:30.792 --> 16:34.875
(motor whirring)

16:39.083 --> 16:41.041
OH.

16:41.083 --> 16:42.625
OH, GOD.

16:42.667 --> 16:46.583
OH, GOD! OH!

16:46.625 --> 16:48.834
OH! OH!

16:48.875 --> 16:52.875
OH! G--OH!

16:56.250 --> 16:59.166
(knock on door)

17:01.083 --> 17:03.166
THIS IS HOW TODAY
SHOULD'VE GONE DOWN.

17:03.208 --> 17:05.667
WHEN WE FOUND OUT THAT
OUR DAUGHTER WAS PREGNANT,

17:05.709 --> 17:08.583
WE SHOULD'VE CRIED
ON EACH OTHER'S SHOULDERS,

17:08.625 --> 17:11.583
WE SHOULD'VE LISTENED TO WHAT
OUR DAUGHTER HAD TO SAY,

17:11.625 --> 17:13.041
AND THEN THE TWO OF US,

17:13.083 --> 17:16.041
TOGETHER, SHOULD HAVE
DISCUSSED HOW TO HANDLE THIS.

17:16.083 --> 17:17.792
THAT'S NOT WHAT HAPPENED.

17:17.834 --> 17:20.041
TALK TO ME.
DEAL WITH THIS.

17:20.083 --> 17:22.667
I DON'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT.

17:22.709 --> 17:26.041
AND I AM DEALING WITH IT.

17:26.083 --> 17:28.667
MAYBE NOT THE WAY
YOU WANT ME TO, BUT...

17:28.709 --> 17:31.000
IT'S THE ONLY WAY I CAN.

17:37.834 --> 17:41.000
I'LL DO IT.

17:41.041 --> 17:43.166
I'LL HAVE THE ABORTION.

17:54.083 --> 17:55.583
(crying)

17:55.625 --> 17:57.041
HER.

17:57.083 --> 17:58.917
OH, YEAH. THAT'S GRIEF.

17:58.959 --> 18:01.041
DEFINITELY.

18:01.083 --> 18:03.834
DEAD HUSBAND? DEAD KID?

18:03.875 --> 18:05.792
IT'S DEAD KID.

18:05.834 --> 18:07.041
IT'S HER FACE.

18:07.083 --> 18:10.959
SHE'S GOT DEAD KID FACE...
LIKE YOU.

18:11.000 --> 18:13.625
I'M SORRY. THAT DIDN'T
COME OUT RIGHT.

18:13.667 --> 18:15.625
NO, IT'S OKAY.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

18:15.667 --> 18:17.834
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
ABOUT MY FACE?

18:17.875 --> 18:19.333
IT'S YOUR EYES.

18:19.375 --> 18:21.333
YOU--YOU'VE BEEN SOMEPLACE

18:21.375 --> 18:23.333
THAT MOST PEOPLE
HAVE NEVER BEEN.

18:23.375 --> 18:24.834
YOU'VE SURVIVED SOMETHING

18:24.875 --> 18:26.834
THAT NO ONE WOULD HAVE
WANTED TO SURVIVE.

18:26.875 --> 18:28.875
IT'S YOUR EYES. IT'S...

18:28.917 --> 18:31.834
THEY'RE, I DON'T KNOW,
EMPTY.

18:31.875 --> 18:34.834
WELL, I MEAN,
THAT COULD BE JUST...

18:34.875 --> 18:37.834
DOESN'T HAVE TO BE
DEAD KID.

18:37.875 --> 18:39.834
IT COULD JUST BE...

18:39.875 --> 18:41.333
BAD LIFE.

18:41.375 --> 18:44.667
NO, IT'S DEAD KID
OR DEAD SOMETHING.

18:44.709 --> 18:47.041
WHAT ABOUT ME?

18:47.083 --> 18:48.333
YOUR FACE?

18:48.375 --> 18:51.000
I MEAN,
I KNOW YOU DON'T KNOW ME,

18:51.041 --> 18:53.000
BUT DO I LOOK DIFFERENT?

18:55.041 --> 18:57.625
YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU'RE IN SHOCK, NATHAN.

18:59.417 --> 19:02.125
YOU LOOK LIKE
SOMETHING BAD HAPPENED.

19:06.917 --> 19:09.583
IT'S REALLY NICE OF YOU
TO SIT HERE, YOU KNOW,

19:09.625 --> 19:11.583
BUT YOU DON'T--
YOU DON'T HAVE TO STAY.

19:11.625 --> 19:13.583
I'M SURE THAT YOU HAVE
SOMEPLACE TO BE.

19:13.625 --> 19:17.500
UH... NO, ACTUALLY.
I DON'T.

19:17.542 --> 19:19.959
OKAY.

19:20.000 --> 19:22.000
OKAY.

19:25.959 --> 19:28.041
SORRY.

19:28.083 --> 19:30.542
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE
AT THE GYM.

19:30.583 --> 19:33.041
I JUST CAME TO GET
THE REST OF MY STUFF.

19:33.083 --> 19:34.417
YEAH, WELL, OKAY.

19:36.083 --> 19:39.542
I BOUGHT THE LATEX JUMPSUIT.

19:39.583 --> 19:42.000
FOR ME.
YOU BOUGHT IT FOR ME.

19:43.458 --> 19:45.959
WHAT, ARE YOU GONNA HAVE
SOME OTHER WOMAN WEAR IT?

19:46.000 --> 19:48.417
WELL, SO SHOULD I
GIVE IT TO YOU

19:48.458 --> 19:50.750
SO YOU COULD WEAR IT
FOR SOME OTHER GUY?

19:50.792 --> 19:53.041
COOPER, WE CAN DO THIS.
WE LIKED EACH OTHER ONCE.

19:53.083 --> 19:54.834
ACTUALLY, WE DIDN'T.

19:54.875 --> 19:57.000
WE DISLIKED EACH OTHER,
AND THEN WE HAD SEX,

19:57.041 --> 19:59.000
AND THEN WE FELL IN LOVE.

19:59.041 --> 20:02.041
WE NEVER LIKED EACH OTHER.

20:02.083 --> 20:05.000
I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

20:05.041 --> 20:08.333
I THINK YOU SHOULD LEAVE
THE PRACTICE.

20:08.375 --> 20:11.333
WHAT?
I'LL TAKE OUT A LOAN.
I'LL SELL MY CAR.

20:11.375 --> 20:14.750
I'LL DO WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO BUY YOU OUT.
NO.

20:14.792 --> 20:16.750
NO?
NO. I'M BUILDING A BUSINESS.

20:16.792 --> 20:19.041
I DON'T CARE
IF YOU WERE THERE FIRST.

20:19.083 --> 20:22.375
I BELONG THERE JUST AS MUCH AS
YOU DO. I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

20:22.417 --> 20:25.041
(hangers clatter)
USELESS, STUPID LOVE.

20:25.083 --> 20:26.208
WHAT?

20:26.250 --> 20:28.041
USELESS, STUPID LOVE!

20:28.083 --> 20:30.000
WASTED TIME.

20:30.041 --> 20:33.041
JUST TAKE YOUR LATEX JUMPSUIT.
FIND ANOTHER WOMAN.

20:33.083 --> 20:36.041
HAVE A BLAST WITH IT!
OH, I C--
I WILL! I CAN'T WAIT.

20:36.083 --> 20:38.792
THAT'S MY TOWEL YOU'RE WEARING.
I WANT IT BACK.

20:38.834 --> 20:40.458
(door closes)

20:40.500 --> 20:42.667
(Lynn) OH, GOD! OH, GOD!

20:42.709 --> 20:44.250
YOU'RE DOING GREAT, LYNN.

20:44.291 --> 20:47.041
YEAH. I FEEL GREAT.

20:47.083 --> 20:50.041
UH, WE--WE COULD CHANGE
THE MUSIC.

20:50.083 --> 20:52.709
WE HAVEN'T LISTENED TO
"CHIRPING BIRDS" YET.

20:52.750 --> 20:54.709
I JUST WANTED THIS
TO BE BEAUTIFUL, YOU KNOW?

20:54.750 --> 20:56.083
ALL MY BOOKS SAID

20:56.125 --> 20:59.041
THAT THE WAY A CHILD
COMES INTO THE WORLD

20:59.083 --> 21:00.500
SHAPES THEM FOR LIFE.

21:00.542 --> 21:03.500
I JUST WANT TO GIVE HIM
THE BEST CHANCE

21:03.542 --> 21:05.500
THAT HE CAN HAVE, YOU KNOW?
MM-HMM.

21:05.542 --> 21:07.500
I-I DON'T WANT TO SHAPE HIM

21:07.542 --> 21:11.709
TO BE SOME ANGRY
OR--OR SCARED... (groans)

21:11.750 --> 21:13.083
DAMN IT.

21:13.125 --> 21:14.917
OH.

21:14.959 --> 21:18.125
I WANT HIM TO HAVE
A GOOD LIFE.

21:18.166 --> 21:20.959
OKAY, LOOK... NO MATTER
HOW TODAY WORKS OUT,

21:21.000 --> 21:23.709
EVEN IF YOU DECIDE
YOU CAN'T TAKE THE PAIN,

21:23.750 --> 21:26.041
YOU'RE STILL GONNA HAVE
PLENTY OF OPPORTUNITIES

21:26.083 --> 21:27.959
TO SHAPE YOUR CHILD'S LIFE.

21:28.000 --> 21:31.000
SO CAN I GIVE YOU SOMETHING
TO HELP WITH THE PAIN?

21:31.041 --> 21:34.041
NO. JUST GIVE ME
THE CHIRPING BIRDS.
OKAY.

21:34.083 --> 21:36.250
YEAH.

21:36.291 --> 21:38.041
(birds chirp)

21:38.083 --> 21:41.041
HOW MANY HAVE YOU DONE?

21:41.083 --> 21:45.041
MORE THAN I CAN COUNT.

21:45.083 --> 21:46.792
AND THEY'VE ALL...

21:46.834 --> 21:48.041
THEY'VE TURNED OUT...

21:48.083 --> 21:50.041
WELL, "FINE"
ISN'T THE WORD I'D USE,

21:50.083 --> 21:52.458
BUT WITHOUT COMPLICATIONS.

21:52.500 --> 21:56.291
MY DAUGHTER'S HAVING
AN ABORTION TOMORROW.

21:56.333 --> 22:01.000
THAT IN AND OF ITSELF
IS A COMPLICATION.

22:01.041 --> 22:04.625
SAM, IS IT WEIRD
THAT IT'S ME... DOING IT?

22:04.667 --> 22:06.625
NO.
WOULD YOU PREFER
THAT I GET A--

22:06.667 --> 22:10.041
I'D UNDERSTAND IF--
NO, YOU DO IT.

22:10.083 --> 22:13.041
YOU DO IT THE BEST YOU HAVE
EVER DONE ANYTHING.

22:13.083 --> 22:15.709
DO IT LIKE YOUR LIFE
DEPENDS ON IT.

22:15.750 --> 22:18.166
(voice breaks) IT'S MAYA.

22:21.208 --> 22:25.041
OH. OH. UGH.

22:25.083 --> 22:26.417
COLIN, WHAT HAPPENED?

22:26.458 --> 22:29.041
SOMETHING'S WRONG.
I-I TOLD 'EM TO CALL YOU. I--

22:29.083 --> 22:31.041
I KNOW YOU WANTED TO TAKE
THE BOLT OUT.

22:31.083 --> 22:34.125
YOU TOLD ME THE ANTIBIOTICS
WERE TOO RISKY, BUT I W--
THIS ISN'T EVEN
THE RIGHT DOSAGE.

22:34.166 --> 22:36.625
DR. FIFE LOWERED IT. HE--
IT WAS--

22:36.667 --> 22:39.000
HE SAID
IT WAS DAMAGING MY NERVES

22:39.041 --> 22:42.333
AND HE SAID THAT HIS ARM
WOULDN'T WORK AND--OHH.

22:42.375 --> 22:45.041
(vomits)
DAMN IT.
THE INFECTION IS SPREADING.

22:45.083 --> 22:47.750
GET ME A CENTRAL LINE KIT.
(groans)

22:53.083 --> 22:55.959
YOU HAVE GOT TO GET
THAT BOLT OUT.
I'LL TAKE IT UNDER ADVISEMENT.

22:56.000 --> 22:57.959
YOU--IT--
THIS IS HIS LIFE,

22:58.000 --> 23:00.458
AND YOU ARE SO CONCERNED
WITH YOUR INVENTION.

23:00.500 --> 23:01.834
IT'S WHAT COLIN WANTED.

23:01.875 --> 23:03.375
IT'S WHAT YOU SOLD HIM.

23:03.417 --> 23:05.375
NAOMI WAS RIGHT ABOUT YOU.

23:05.417 --> 23:06.834
YOU'RE FULL OF CRAP.

23:06.875 --> 23:10.041
YOU DON'T WANT TO FIX HIS ARM.
YOU WANT TO FIX YOUR LEGS.

23:10.083 --> 23:12.041
NO. I ALREADY TRIED,
AND I CAN'T.

23:12.083 --> 23:15.083
OKAY, IS THAT SUPPOSED TO
MAKE ME FEEL SORRY FOR YOU?

23:15.125 --> 23:18.083
I'M NOT DOING THIS FOR ME.
I'VE ACCEPTED WHAT I LOST

23:18.125 --> 23:21.166
AND I'LL ACCEPT IT FOR COLIN
AS WELL, BUT NOT YET.
YOU JUST DON'T WANT TO SEE IT.

23:21.208 --> 23:24.000
MAYBE, AND MAYBE THERE IS
SOMETHING OUT THERE

23:24.041 --> 23:26.000
THAT WE HAVEN'T
THOUGHT OF YET.

23:26.041 --> 23:29.041
LOOK, I'M NOT GOOD AT ASKING
FOR HELP, BUT I'M ASKING.

23:29.083 --> 23:32.000
MY PATIENT WANTS TO PICK UP
HIS LIFE WERE IT LEFT OFF.

23:32.041 --> 23:34.000
IT MAY NOT BE
WHAT YOU WOULD CHOOSE,

23:34.041 --> 23:36.041
BUT IT'S WHAT HE CHOOSES.

23:36.083 --> 23:37.834
SO DO IT FOR HIM.

23:40.208 --> 23:43.208
(woman speaking indistinctly
over p.a.)

23:43.250 --> 23:45.333
(thud)

23:47.125 --> 23:49.291
(thud)

23:51.542 --> 23:54.291
YOU DID NOT JUST SEE THAT.

23:54.333 --> 23:57.041
ISN'T THAT WHAT YOU
WERE WEARING YESTERDAY?

23:57.083 --> 23:59.291
UH, YEAH. JUST...
HELPING OUT A FRIEND.

23:59.333 --> 24:02.542
WANT ME TO LOAN YOU
SOMETHING?
DID YOU MOVE
ALL YOUR STUFF IN HERE?

24:02.583 --> 24:04.917
I SOLD MY PLACE.

24:04.959 --> 24:08.041
I KNOW.
IT WAS A ROOKIE MISTAKE.

24:08.083 --> 24:11.125
GIVING IT ALL UP FOR A GUY,
MOVING INTO COOPER'S APARTMENT,

24:11.166 --> 24:13.125
MOVING INTO THE PRACTICE
WHERE HE WORKED.

24:13.166 --> 24:16.125
(chuckles) I CHANGED MY LIFE
TO BE WITH HIM.

24:16.166 --> 24:18.500
I WENT ALL-IN ON FOREVER.

24:18.542 --> 24:21.000
DOES COOPER KNOW THAT?
NO POINT NOW.

24:21.041 --> 24:22.542
HE WANTS ME OUT.

24:22.583 --> 24:25.792
HE WANTS TO PRETEND WE DIDN'T
HAPPEN, THAT I DON'T EXIST.

24:25.834 --> 24:30.959
WELL, HE THINKS THAT'S GONNA
MAKE HIM FEEL BETTER.

24:31.000 --> 24:32.500
BUT IT WON'T.

24:32.542 --> 24:34.959
IT'LL JUST MAKE HIM FEEL...

24:35.000 --> 24:36.083
A-ALONE.

24:36.125 --> 24:39.917
I KNOW THE FEELING.

24:39.959 --> 24:42.500
ME, TOO.

24:42.542 --> 24:44.083
SO...

24:44.125 --> 24:47.709
DO YOU WANT TO WEAR SLUTTY
OR PROFESSIONAL?

24:47.750 --> 24:50.125
(Lynn) OH, DELL!

24:50.166 --> 24:52.834
DELL!

24:52.875 --> 24:54.834
THIS IS A BIG ONE!

24:54.875 --> 24:56.834
STILL?
I...

24:56.875 --> 24:59.041
AAH!

24:59.083 --> 25:01.458
♪♪♪

25:01.500 --> 25:05.000
(man) ♪ IT SURE IS HARD
TO BE APART ♪

25:05.041 --> 25:06.750
♪ BUT OUR TV SHOW... ♪

25:06.792 --> 25:08.834
SO WE'RE HERE.

25:08.875 --> 25:12.041
OKAY. IS EVERYBODY, UH,
SURE ABOUT THIS?

25:12.083 --> 25:14.333
JUST... DO IT.

25:14.375 --> 25:16.417
♪♪♪

25:16.458 --> 25:18.417
MAYA.

25:21.000 --> 25:23.041
♪ DOES SHE STILL KNOW ♪

25:23.083 --> 25:26.000
♪ THEY'RE THE ONES? ♪

25:28.291 --> 25:32.959
♪ HER FAVORITE DAUGHTER'S
FAVORITE SONS ♪

25:33.000 --> 25:34.458
(knock on door)

25:34.500 --> 25:36.542
I COULDN'T STAY UPSTAIRS.

25:36.583 --> 25:38.542
CHARLOTTE?
SHE WON'T LEAVE.

25:38.583 --> 25:40.125
AND THEN SAM AND NAOMI...

25:40.166 --> 25:42.458
I FEEL LIKE I SHOULD--I SHOULD
DO SOMETHING FOR THEM,

25:42.500 --> 25:46.000
LIKE I SHOULD SEND FOOD
OR SOMETHING, BUT...
WELL, NOBODY'S SICK.

25:46.041 --> 25:48.000
SENDING A TUB OF SOUP
ISN'T GONNA HELP.

25:48.041 --> 25:51.041
I KNOW. WHAT AM I SUPPOSED
TO DO, PETE?
ABOUT CHARLOTTE?

25:51.083 --> 25:54.041
ACCEPT IT, MOVE ON. I MEAN,
THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN DO.

25:54.083 --> 25:57.041
SAM AND NAOMI?
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.

25:57.083 --> 26:00.166
I... MAYBE THAT'S WHY
PEOPLE SEND SOUP.

26:00.208 --> 26:03.000
NOTHING YOU CAN DO.

26:05.959 --> 26:08.083
♪ YOU SAY YOU'RE WORRIED ♪

26:08.125 --> 26:10.208
♪ I SAY I AM, TOO ♪

26:10.250 --> 26:13.041
♪ IT'S OKAY, IT'S WHAT
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO DO ♪

26:13.083 --> 26:16.250
DO YOU REMEMBER THE DAY
MAYA LOST HER FIRST TOOTH?

26:16.291 --> 26:19.417
IT FELL OUT IN THE YARD.

26:19.458 --> 26:22.041
WE SPENT ABOUT FOUR HOURS
LOOKING FOR THAT THING

26:22.083 --> 26:24.041
BECAUSE WITHOUT PROOF,

26:24.083 --> 26:26.375
THE TOOTH FAIRY
WOULDN'T PAY UP.

26:26.417 --> 26:30.208
♪♪♪

26:30.250 --> 26:32.125
AND THEN THERE'S TODAY.

26:32.166 --> 26:34.125
♪♪♪

26:34.166 --> 26:37.041
(sighs) YOU KNOW,
WE'RE GONNA GET THROUGH THIS.

26:37.083 --> 26:40.041
ONCE THIS WHOLE THING
IS OVER AND DONE,

26:40.083 --> 26:43.041
WE'RE GONNA GET BACK THERE.

26:43.083 --> 26:44.041
(exhales)

26:44.083 --> 26:45.750
SAY SOMETHING!

26:45.792 --> 26:47.291
ANYTHING!

26:47.333 --> 26:49.291
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME
TO SAY?

26:49.333 --> 26:52.208
YOU WANT ME TO SAY THAT I DID
THE WRONG THING? OKAY.

26:52.250 --> 26:54.041
I DID THE WRONG THING.

26:54.083 --> 26:57.041
DO I BELIEVE
THAT I'M GOING TO HELL

26:57.083 --> 27:00.041
FOR FORCING OUR DAUGHTER
TO HAVE AN ABORTION?

27:00.083 --> 27:03.041
(voice breaking) ABSOLUTELY.

27:03.083 --> 27:06.041
DO I REGRET DOING
WHAT I HAD TO DO? NO.

27:06.083 --> 27:08.041
♪♪♪

27:08.083 --> 27:09.458
I WOULD DO ANYTHING,

27:09.500 --> 27:12.041
I WOULD GIVE MY LIFE
TO PROTECT HER,

27:12.083 --> 27:14.959
AND IF IT MEANS THAT I'M
GOING TO HELL, THEN FINE.

27:15.000 --> 27:16.166
I'M GOING TO HELL.

27:16.208 --> 27:18.542
OH, NAOMI--
I FAILED, SAM.

27:18.583 --> 27:21.000
(sobs) I FAILED...

27:21.041 --> 27:24.500
FIRST IN OUR MARRIAGE,
AND NOW AT BEING A MOTHER.

27:24.542 --> 27:28.542
NO. THIS IS ON BOTH OF US.

27:28.583 --> 27:31.583
I THOUGHT I TAUGHT HER
RIGHT FROM WRONG.

27:31.625 --> 27:33.709
BUT SHE DIDN'T LISTEN.

27:33.750 --> 27:37.000
IT'S LIKE NOTHING I DID
MADE ANY DIFFERENCE.

27:38.625 --> 27:41.959
I FAILED.

27:42.000 --> 27:45.834
♪♪♪

27:50.583 --> 27:52.375
YOU'RE GONNA EXPERIENCE
SOME DISCOMFORT

27:52.417 --> 27:56.041
AND SOME BLEEDING AFTERWARD
FOR ABOUT A WEEK.

27:56.083 --> 27:59.583
THE ENTIRE PROCEDURE
WON'T TAKE LONG.

27:59.625 --> 28:02.417
I'M GONNA USE THIS INSTRUMENT
ATTACHED TO SUCTION

28:02.458 --> 28:04.041
TO REMOVE THE PREGNANCY.

28:04.083 --> 28:05.792
YOU'LL HAVE SOME CRAMPING,

28:05.834 --> 28:08.041
JUST FOR A FEW SECONDS.

28:08.083 --> 28:11.208
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

28:11.250 --> 28:13.208
MAYA, IT'S REALLY--

28:13.250 --> 28:16.875
IT'S IMPORTANT THAT YOU TELL ME
WHETHER OR NOT YOU UNDERSTAND.

28:19.625 --> 28:22.041
NO.

28:22.083 --> 28:23.750
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

28:23.792 --> 28:25.583
OKAY.

28:25.625 --> 28:28.000
ASK ME.
(clears throat)

28:30.083 --> 28:32.417
ANYTHING YOU WANT TO KNOW.

28:34.083 --> 28:37.792
ALL MY LIFE, MY MOM TOLD ME
THAT SHE WOULD NEVER...

28:37.834 --> 28:39.667
NEVER DO THIS,

28:39.709 --> 28:41.667
THAT FROM THE SECOND
THEY'RE CONCEIVED,

28:41.709 --> 28:44.375
A BABY IS A LIFE--
A GIFT FROM GOD--

28:44.417 --> 28:46.792
AND THAT ABORTION IS WRONG...

28:46.834 --> 28:48.625
THAT IT'S MURDER.

28:48.667 --> 28:52.500
YES. THAT'S WHAT
YOUR MOTHER BELIEVES.

28:52.542 --> 28:55.000
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

28:55.041 --> 28:57.625
WHAT DO YOU BELIEVE?

28:59.208 --> 29:04.250
I BELIEVE THAT UNTIL A FETUS
CAN SURVIVE ON ITS OWN

29:04.291 --> 29:05.792
OUTSIDE THE MOTHER'S BODY,

29:05.834 --> 29:07.792
THAT IT IS NOT A LIFE.

29:07.834 --> 29:10.291
I BELIEVE THAT LIFE
BEGINS AT BIRTH.

29:10.333 --> 29:13.583
SO YOU THINK MY MOM
WAS WRONG BEFORE

29:13.625 --> 29:17.458
AND THAT SHE'S RIGHT NOW
BECAUSE SHE WANTS ME TO DO THIS?

29:17.500 --> 29:21.041
I THINK THAT YOUR MOTHER
AND I THINK DIFFERENTLY.

29:21.083 --> 29:23.041
THAT DOESN'T HELP ME.

29:23.083 --> 29:25.834
MAYA, I CAN'T HELP YOU
WITH THIS DECISION.

29:25.875 --> 29:27.834
I CAN AND WILL GIVE YOU
AN ABORTION

29:27.875 --> 29:29.834
OR I CAN OFFER OTHER OPTIONS

29:29.875 --> 29:31.834
AND SEE YOU THROUGH
THIS PREGNANCY.

29:31.875 --> 29:34.083
BUT I CAN'T HELP YOU DECIDE.

29:36.083 --> 29:39.041
I'M 15 YEARS OLD.
WHICH IS WHY YOU SHOULDN'T
HAVE BEEN HAVING SEX

29:39.083 --> 29:40.750
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

29:40.792 --> 29:43.291
AND I SAY THAT
AS YOUR AUNT ADDIE, OKAY?

29:43.333 --> 29:46.041
BUT... AS YOUR DOCTOR, MAYA,

29:46.083 --> 29:49.792
SINCE YOU ALREADY
HAVE HAD SEX

29:49.834 --> 29:52.792
AND BECAUSE
YOU ARE PREGNANT...

29:52.834 --> 29:54.917
MAYA...

29:54.959 --> 29:56.500
I KNOW THIS IS HARD.

29:56.542 --> 29:59.083
I KNOW THAT THIS IS...

29:59.125 --> 30:02.750
AN UNIMAGINABLY DIFFICULT,
GROWN-UP DECISION,

30:02.792 --> 30:05.166
AND IT'S NOT FAIR
THAT YOU HAVE TO MAKE IT.

30:05.208 --> 30:07.166
BUT YOU DID A GROWN-UP THING.

30:07.208 --> 30:10.166
AND NOW YOU ARE IN
A GROWN-UP PREDICAMENT.

30:10.208 --> 30:12.166
SO NOW IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT I BELIEVE

30:12.208 --> 30:14.667
OR WHAT YOUR MOTHER BELIEVES.

30:14.709 --> 30:17.667
WHAT MATTERS IS WHAT
YOU BELIEVE. IT'S UP TO YOU.

30:17.709 --> 30:19.333
BUT MY MOM SAID I--

30:19.375 --> 30:21.333
UNTIL THE 24th WEEK
OF PREGNANCY,

30:21.375 --> 30:25.083
WHAT A WOMAN DOES WITH
HER OWN BODY IS HER BUSINESS.

30:25.125 --> 30:28.792
IT'S LAW. IT'S THE LAW, MAYA.

30:28.834 --> 30:31.834
AND OF LOT OF FINE WOMEN
FOUGHT A LONG TIME

30:31.875 --> 30:36.041
TO GIVE YOU THE RIGHT TO DO
WHAT YOU THINK IS BEST.

30:36.083 --> 30:39.083
YOUR BODY, YOUR CHOICE.

30:39.125 --> 30:42.959
MAYA, YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU WANT TO DO.

30:43.000 --> 30:44.959
IN YOUR HEART, IN YOUR GUT,

30:45.000 --> 30:46.959
YOU KNOW WHICH WAY
YOU WANT TO GO.

30:47.000 --> 30:49.041
I'VE DONE THIS ENOUGH
TO KNOW THAT.

30:49.083 --> 30:51.792
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU WANT TO DO.

30:51.834 --> 30:54.834
OKAY? YOU JUST NEED
TO TELL ME.

30:54.875 --> 30:59.000
(Lady of the Sunshine's
"Silver Revolver" playing)

30:59.041 --> 31:01.041
♪ HEY, MAMA ♪

31:01.083 --> 31:03.000
I KNOW YOU'RE TIRED,
BUT ON THIS NEXT CONTRACTION,

31:03.041 --> 31:05.125
I'M REALLY GONNA NEED YOU
TO PUSH.
I CAN'T.

31:05.166 --> 31:07.250
YES, YOU CAN.
IT HURTS.

31:07.291 --> 31:09.250
COME ON, LYNN. THIS IS
WHAT YOU WANTED, OKAY?

31:09.291 --> 31:12.250
YOU CAN DO IT.
(crying) I WAS WRONG, OKAY?
MY BIRTH PLAN IS STUPID.

31:12.291 --> 31:14.750
IT'S NOT WORKING. I'VE BEEN
AWAKE FOR THREE DAYS.

31:14.792 --> 31:17.208
I FEEL LIKE I'VE BEEN
RUN OVER BY A TRAIN.

31:17.250 --> 31:20.250
OKAY, JUST TURN OFF
THE HIPPIE-ASS FLUTE MUSIC

31:20.291 --> 31:22.750
AND GIVE ME SOME DRUGS, NOW!
O-OKAY, OKAY.

31:22.792 --> 31:25.542
I-I CAN'T GIVE YOU DRUGS.
BUT I WANT DRUGS!

31:25.583 --> 31:28.375
OKAY? YOU SAID
I COULD CHANGE MY MIND!

31:28.417 --> 31:32.041
OKAY. I KNOW IT HURTS,
BUT WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

31:32.083 --> 31:35.041
AND THAT'S WHY I CAN'T
GIVE YOU ANY DRUGS.
PLEASE STOP SAYING THAT.
(sobs)

31:35.083 --> 31:36.583
OKAY, LISTEN...

31:36.625 --> 31:39.041
YOU HAD A PLAN,
AND YOU'VE STUCK TO IT,

31:39.083 --> 31:41.834
AND NOT EVERYONE CAN DO THAT,
BUT YOU DID.

31:41.875 --> 31:45.041
AND I AM HERE WITH YOU, AND WE
ARE GOING TO GET THROUGH THIS.

31:45.083 --> 31:48.375
I PROMISE.
(whimpers) OH.

31:48.417 --> 31:51.000
NOW PUSH.

31:51.041 --> 31:52.458
(screaming)

31:52.500 --> 31:55.625
OBVIOUSLY THE RESULTS
WEREN'T WHAT WE HOPED.

31:55.667 --> 31:58.709
I KNOW IT WAS JUST METAL.

31:58.750 --> 32:01.041
BUT... I SWEAR,

32:01.083 --> 32:04.041
WHEN I CAUGHT THAT TENNIS BALL,
I COULD FEEL IT.

32:04.083 --> 32:06.875
IT WAS FUZZY,
JUST A LITTLE BIT OF GIVE.

32:06.917 --> 32:09.959
WE HAVE TO REMOVE THE BOLT
AND A MARGIN OF TISSUE

32:10.000 --> 32:12.041
TO MAKE SURE
THE INFECTION IS GONE.

32:12.083 --> 32:16.875
AND WE MAY NEED TO REMOVE
THE REST OF YOUR ARM,

32:16.917 --> 32:19.667
POSSIBLY ALL THE WAY UP
TO YOUR SHOULDER.

32:19.709 --> 32:22.250
THAT'S ONE OPTION. IT WOULD
DEFINITELY SAVE YOUR LIFE.

32:22.291 --> 32:24.750
BUT...
BUT WHAT?

32:24.792 --> 32:26.750
THERE'S BEEN SOME SUCCESS

32:26.792 --> 32:29.041
WITH BIODEGRADABLE
ANTIBIOTIC IMPLANTS.

32:29.083 --> 32:30.834
IT'S RISKY.
IT REQUIRES SURGERY.

32:30.875 --> 32:32.709
WE'D HAVE TO IMPLANT
THE ANTIBIOTICS

32:32.750 --> 32:35.291
DIRECTLY NEXT TO
THE BOLT SITE.

32:35.333 --> 32:38.333
GIVE YOU THE LIFE YOU WANT,
LET YOU DANCE AT YOUR WEDDING.

32:38.375 --> 32:40.333
♪ OH, LOVER ♪

32:40.375 --> 32:41.917
(exhales deeply)

32:43.792 --> 32:45.583
♪ PASS THE SILVER ♪

32:45.625 --> 32:47.542
♪ SILVER REVOLVER ♪

32:47.583 --> 32:49.542
(woman) OKAY, YOU GUYS READY?
(laughs)

32:49.583 --> 32:51.375
(children laugh)
OKAY, SLOW DOWN.

32:51.417 --> 32:52.917
WE NEVER HAD KIDS.

32:52.959 --> 32:55.041
MY WIFE WANTED KIDS.

32:55.083 --> 32:57.667
♪♪♪

32:57.709 --> 33:00.959
I THINK WE SHOULD LEAVE.

33:01.000 --> 33:02.875
LOOK, YOU--YOU HAVE
LOST SOMEONE HERE

33:02.917 --> 33:04.583
WHO'S VERY IMPORTANT TO YOU.

33:04.625 --> 33:06.333
AND YOU'RE AFRAID

33:06.375 --> 33:08.959
THAT IF YOU GO HOME
AND WALK INTO AN EMPTY ROOM,

33:09.000 --> 33:11.917
THAT'LL MEAN
YOU'RE REALLY ALONE.
I WILL BE ALONE.

33:11.959 --> 33:13.709
NO. I'LL...

33:13.750 --> 33:15.375
I'LL GO WITH YOU.

33:15.417 --> 33:20.000
♪ IT'S ALL IN MY HEAD,
IT'S ALL IN MY HEAD ♪

33:21.875 --> 33:23.375
♪ IT'S ALL IN MY HEAD ♪

33:23.417 --> 33:27.000
♪ IT'S ALL IN MY HEAD ♪

33:30.000 --> 33:31.917
I DIDN'T DO IT.

33:31.959 --> 33:33.208
WHAT?

33:33.250 --> 33:35.041
I'M NOT HAVING
AN ABORTION.

33:35.083 --> 33:38.375
♪ IT'S IN MY... ♪

33:38.417 --> 33:41.041
MOM! STOP.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

33:41.083 --> 33:42.375
NAOMI.

33:42.417 --> 33:44.041
OW! OW!
HEY!

33:44.083 --> 33:46.458
IF YOU'RE COMING IN,
YOU BETTER BE TAKING PICTURES.

33:46.500 --> 33:49.000
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?
ADDISON, A LITTLE HELP.

33:49.041 --> 33:51.625
I AM NOT GONNA LET YOU
RUIN YOUR LIFE, LITTLE GIRL.
ALL RIGHT, LYNN.
NOW COME ON. PUSH.

33:51.667 --> 33:54.000
YOU THINK YOU KNOW WHAT
YOU WANT? YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

33:54.041 --> 33:56.750
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT YOU WANT.
LOOK AT THAT. LOOK AT THAT.

33:56.792 --> 33:58.458
OKAY.

33:58.500 --> 34:01.333
(cries) HI. HI.
(baby coos)

34:01.375 --> 34:03.333
♪♪♪

34:03.375 --> 34:05.250
BUT LOOK AT THAT.

34:05.291 --> 34:08.041
(fusses)

34:08.083 --> 34:11.041
♪ ALL I'VE EVER BEEN TO MYSELF ♪

34:11.083 --> 34:13.125
♪ IS MY OWN ENEMY ♪

34:18.125 --> 34:19.834
(Maya) MOM.

34:19.875 --> 34:22.333
MOM. MOMMY!

34:35.875 --> 34:39.458
(crying)
I CAN'T. I'M SORRY.

34:39.500 --> 34:42.041
I-I CAN'T.

34:42.083 --> 34:43.792
(Addison) NAI.
IT'S OKAY. SHH.

34:43.834 --> 34:45.709
(sobbing)

34:45.750 --> 34:51.250
(sighs) SHH, SHH, SHH,
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH.

34:51.291 --> 34:53.333
NAOMI. NAI.

34:53.375 --> 34:55.333
THIS ISN'T
THE END OF THE WORLD.

34:55.375 --> 34:57.834
YOU WILL GET PAST THIS.
I NEED TO GET OUTTA HERE.

34:57.875 --> 35:01.041
DON'T DO THIS. YOU DON'T WANT TO
TURN YOUR BACK ON YOUR CHILD.

35:01.083 --> 35:04.041
YOU JUST SHUT UP!
JUST FOR ONCE, JUST SHUT UP!

35:04.083 --> 35:07.458
FOR A MINUTE, FOR NOW,
SHUT UP!

35:13.959 --> 35:17.542
WELL... THIS IS FUN.

35:19.667 --> 35:21.500
IT'S FINE.

35:21.542 --> 35:24.667
(chuckles) BET YOU'D BE
A GREAT DATE.

35:24.709 --> 35:27.709
IF MY WIFE HADN'T JUST DIED,
I'D ASK YOU OUT.

35:27.750 --> 35:31.291
(chuckles)
THAT WAS FUNNY.

35:36.083 --> 35:38.208
LET'S TRY
WALKING THROUGH THE DOOR.

35:51.583 --> 35:53.750
WE THOUGHT SHE HAD A COLD.

35:53.792 --> 35:57.417
A FEW YEARS AGO, WE WERE
SUPPOSED TO GO ON A SKIING TRIP,

35:57.458 --> 35:59.417
AND WE THOUGHT SHE HAD A COLD.

35:59.458 --> 36:01.625
BUT IT NEVER WENT AWAY.

36:01.667 --> 36:03.041
CANCER.

36:03.083 --> 36:06.333
AND I-I KNEW IT WAS COMING.
I KNEW IT.

36:06.375 --> 36:07.709
SO I SLEPT THERE.

36:07.750 --> 36:10.792
I SLEPT IN THAT HOSPITAL
WITH HER FOR MONTHS.

36:10.834 --> 36:12.417
THIS HOUSE...

36:12.458 --> 36:15.542
IT WAS THE LAST TIME
WE WERE HAPPY TOGETHER.

36:15.583 --> 36:18.583
(Diane Birch's "Magic View"
playing)

36:21.792 --> 36:25.041
♪ TURNING ♪

36:25.083 --> 36:27.041
♪ TURNING ARE THE TABLES... ♪

36:27.083 --> 36:29.041
ONE STEP AT A TIME.

36:29.083 --> 36:32.542
♪ HERE BEFORE ME ♪

36:32.583 --> 36:38.041
♪ OH, BUT YOU'RE SO LOVELY ♪

36:38.083 --> 36:39.542
♪ LOVELY AS YOU ARE ♪

36:39.583 --> 36:43.041
♪ I KNOW YOU'LL LEAVE ME ♪

36:43.083 --> 36:44.750
(inhales deeply)

36:44.792 --> 36:51.041
♪ HIGH UP IN A TREE
I CAN'T CLIMB DOWN ♪

36:51.083 --> 36:52.750
I THOUGHT...

36:52.792 --> 36:55.041
I THOUGHT IT WOULD KILL ME.

36:55.083 --> 36:58.041
STEPPING BACK INTO THIS HOUSE,
I THOUGHT IT WOULD--

36:58.083 --> 37:00.625
I THOUGHT IT WOULD
MAKE HER MORE GONE.

37:00.667 --> 37:04.875
BUT... SHE'S HERE.

37:04.917 --> 37:08.041
SHE LOVED IT HERE.

37:08.083 --> 37:10.458
AND WE WERE HAPPY
IN THIS HOUSE.

37:10.500 --> 37:13.166
THANK YOU.

37:13.208 --> 37:16.166
♪ BURNING ♪

37:16.208 --> 37:17.709
(sniffles)

37:17.750 --> 37:18.917
VIOLET?

37:18.959 --> 37:20.917
THAT DEAD KID FACE?

37:20.959 --> 37:23.792
♪ I'M TURNING ♪

37:23.834 --> 37:25.041
♪ TURNING INTO ME ♪

37:25.083 --> 37:27.208
IT'S NOT MY SON.

37:27.250 --> 37:28.875
♪ ...HEAVEN ♪

37:28.917 --> 37:32.041
MY SON ISN'T DEAD.

37:32.083 --> 37:34.917
IT'S ME.

37:34.959 --> 37:37.959
I WALKED AWAY FROM MY SON.

37:38.000 --> 37:40.625
I GAVE HIM AWAY.

37:40.667 --> 37:43.959
SO... I DON'T HAVE
A BAG OF HIS STUFF

37:44.000 --> 37:47.709
OR A LAST PLACE
WHERE WE WERE HAPPY.

37:47.750 --> 37:50.125
HE NEVER
GOT TO SEE ME HAPPY.

37:50.166 --> 37:53.041
(crying) HE'S ONLY
6 MONTHS OLD,

37:53.083 --> 37:55.709
AND NOW I'VE LET
A TOTAL STRANGER

37:55.750 --> 37:57.250
BELIEVE HE'S DEAD.

37:57.291 --> 37:59.250
I HAVE A SON...

37:59.291 --> 38:02.208
AND HIS NAME IS LUCAS.

38:02.250 --> 38:05.125
(crying)

38:05.166 --> 38:08.250
♪♪♪

38:08.291 --> 38:10.041
(engine revs)

38:10.083 --> 38:12.333
(tires squeal)

38:12.375 --> 38:15.750
WAS I TOO NICE TO YOU, HUH?
IS THAT WHAT HAPPENED?

38:15.792 --> 38:18.291
YOU THOUGHT
I WAS A NICE GUY, HUH?
DR. BENNETT--

38:18.333 --> 38:20.583
SHUT UP. SHUT THE...
YOU SHOULDA BEEN AFRAID OF ME.

38:20.625 --> 38:22.125
YOU SHOULDA BEEN TERRIFIED.

38:22.166 --> 38:24.083
MY FACE SHOULDA BEEN
IN YOUR HEAD

38:24.125 --> 38:26.083
EVERY SINGLE MOMENT
YOU WERE WITH MAYA.

38:26.125 --> 38:28.875
SO LOOK AT ME RIGHT NOW.

38:28.917 --> 38:32.291
LOOK LONG AND HARD
AND REMEMBER ME SAYING,

38:32.333 --> 38:34.291
YOU WILL NEVER
HURT MAYA AGAIN.

38:34.333 --> 38:35.667
OKAY.

38:35.709 --> 38:37.750
YOU GOT MY DAUGHTER PREGNANT.

38:37.792 --> 38:39.750
SO HELP ME GOD, IF I COULD--

38:39.792 --> 38:41.667
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

38:41.709 --> 38:43.083
MAYA'S PREGNANT?

38:48.834 --> 38:50.792
YOU DIDN'T KNOW.

38:50.834 --> 38:54.041
(students speaking indistinctly)

38:54.083 --> 38:56.417
DR. BENNETT...

38:56.458 --> 38:58.458
I LOVE HER.

39:07.250 --> 39:09.709
DID YOU EVER FIND YOUR SHOE?

39:09.750 --> 39:12.709
NO. FINISH HELPING
THAT FRIEND?

39:12.750 --> 39:14.375
YEAH, I DID.

39:18.917 --> 39:21.000
I WANT TO PUNCH HIM.

39:21.041 --> 39:23.125
I DIDN'T WANT
A RELATIONSHIP, DAMN IT.

39:23.166 --> 39:25.792
I WAS FINE BEING ALONE.

39:27.792 --> 39:31.834
YOU KNOW WHAT I MISS?
YOUR MARTINIS.

39:31.875 --> 39:34.750
YOU SURE DO KNOW
HOW TO CHANGE A SUBJECT.

39:34.792 --> 39:37.834
NO, I WAS JUST THINKING THAT
YOU HAVE NOWHERE TO GO,

39:37.875 --> 39:40.750
